what is a tag?

a tag is git is like a label or bookmark for a specific commit

tags are most ofter used to mark important points in your project history, like releases (v1.0 or v2.0)

tags are simple and reliable way to keep track of versions and share them with your team or users.

common tag types

releases, miliestones, deployment, hotfixes

git tag v1.0

git tag -a v1.0 -m "version 1.0 release"

git show v1.0

push tags to remote ->  git push origin v1.0 / git push --tags

git push : does not push your tags 

delete tags: git tag -d v1.0

delete tags remotely:  git push origin --delete tag v1.0

update / replace a tag (force push) - if you need to move a tag to a different commit and update the remote, use --force

git tag -f v1.0 <new-commit-hash>

git push --force origin v1.0


